race.comment: WINSTON HILLS (6) raced closer to the speed than usual then pulled out all stops to just get home in a BM72 over this course and distance last time. Six-year-old who is going as well as ever and with Nash standing over him he should be very hard to beat again. DANCE TO THE BOOM (8) led all the way to justify her short quote against the girls over this trip at the Kensington track most recently. Love this stable when they hit winning form. Sparingly raced and still on the ascendency. PEACE OFFICER (5) has placed three from three here. Disappointed last start over this trip at the Kensington track last time out when second-up. Can bounce back in a race that suits. FORMAL DISPLAY (2) raced handy and battled on well for third recently over this distance at Rosehill. Big chance dropping back to midweek company. SYDNEY BOWLER (11) strips fitter and should go well, although running a strong 1400m is the query.
